The article criticizes a judge in San Francisco for rewriting immigration policy and accuses sanctuary cities of violating federal law. It claims that sanctuary cities prioritize the well-being of criminal immigrants over the safety of citizens and argues that the judge's ruling puts innocent lives at risk. The article also criticizes the judge for overreach and raises concerns about circuit shopping. It expresses confidence in prevailing in the Supreme Court and vows to pursue legal remedies against sanctuary cities and ramp up enforcement to remove criminals and gangs from the country. The article frames the issue as a fight between sovereignty and open borders, the rule of law and lawlessness, and hardworking Americans and those who undermine their safety and freedom.